SIMPLE: forecast
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forecast
<hw>Fore*cast"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
plan beforehand; to scheme; to project.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He shall <qex>forecast</qex> his devices against the
strongholds.</q> <rj><qau>Dan. xi. 24.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To foresee; to calculate beforehand, so as to
provide for; <as>as, to <ex>forecast</ex> the weather; to
<ex>forecast</ex> prices</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is wisdom to consider the end of things before we embark, and
to <qex>forecast</qex> consequences.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forecast</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Forecast
<hw>Fore*cast"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To contrive or plan
beforehand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If it happen as I did <qex>forecast</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forecast</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Forecast
<hw>Fore"cast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Previous contrivance
or determination; predetermination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He makes this difference to arise from the <qex>forecast</qex> and
predetermination of the gods themselves.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A calculation predicting future events; the
foresight of consequences, and provision against them; prevision;
premeditation; <as>as, the weather <ex>forecast</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His calm, deliberate <qex>forecast</qex> better fitted him for the
council than the camp.</q> <rj><qau>Prescott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forecaster</ent>⟦br⟧
